A sub-optimal relay selection algorithm is described as followed three rules, which can reduce the load of computing comparing methods mentioned in [10].

(1)The channel quality between source and partner (received SNR at partner) should larger than threshold \$S_{1}\$;
(2)The user closest to the source user will be selected as the partner;
(3)Users whose channel quality (received SNR at BS) is better than the source should be selected first.

